cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.MA 

This paper deals with game theory and negotiation, which are central topics in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on two-player normal form games with preplay negotiation phases, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The use of conditional offers and the analysis of bargaining power and time value suggest that this paper could also be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The mathematical analysis of the bargaining process and the possible solutions of such games suggest that this paper could also be classified under data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
